The latest MSTest is **4.2.2**. Here are the breaking changes relevant to your project:

## 1. `[ExpectedException]` is removed (compile error)

This is the biggest impact. Your two test methods using `[ExpectedException]` will fail to compile. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## 2. `MSTEST0032` severity upgraded to Warning

Your `Assert.IsTrue(true)` will now emit a **warning** (was Info). It flags always-true assertions as likely mistakes.

## 3. Assert API signature changes

`Assert` methods accepting `message` + `params object[]` now only accept `message`. Use string interpolation instead if you format messages elsewhere.

## 4. Other changes (likely no impact for you)

- `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` (only if you subclass it)
- `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed
- `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>`
- Minimum TFM is net8.0 (you're already there ✅)

---

Would you like me to apply the fixes to your project (upgrade the package and update the test code)?
